text: Novomuslyumovo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Bolsheustyikinsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,063 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 12 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Novomuslyumovo
